Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198505">1985-05-07 15:33:25</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426419&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426419&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

The UCLA CS Department now has a name server for the UCLA.EDU domain,
running on the two hosts UCLA-LOCUS (10.2.0.1) and UCLA-ATS (10.3.0.1).

Our server supports both "regular" and "inverse" queries.  We can handle
any kind of inverse query (not just address-to-name mapping).  We do not
yet do completion queries or QCLASS=ANY.

In order to find any bugs, I would like as many people as possible to
"beat" on our server.  In particular, I would like to know whether
people not directly on the ARPANET are able to get replies from us (we
are having some kind of problem -- possibly due to a bug somewhere in
our LOCUS system's UDP code -- which is preventing me from getting any
kind of response from name servers on class-B Internet addresses.)

If you encounter any unexpected or seemingly erroneous behavior from our
server (including situations where it doesn't seem to respond to you at
all), please send me a message describing the particulars.

Thanks.

-- 
